@notice Deposits ERC20 tokens into the contract
 @param token The address of the ERC20 token
 @param amount The amount of tokens to deposit
 @dev This function should be call by owner but opens for donation

@notice Deposits ERC20 tokens into the contract
	by calling depositToken() multiple times
 @param tokens The addresses of the ERC20 tokens
 @param amounts The amounts of tokens to deposit
 @dev This function should be call by owner but opens for donation
		and reverts if the length of the two arrays are not equal
		or if any of the depositToken() calls reverts

@notice Deposits ERC20 tokens into the contract with permit
 @param token The address of the ERC20 token
 @param amount The amount of tokens to deposit
 @param signature The signature of the permit
 @param deadline The deadline of the permit
 @dev This function should be call by owner but opens for donation
		and reverts if the token is not registered
		or if the permit is invalid

@notice Deposits ERC20 tokens into the contract with permit
	by calling depositTokenSig() multiple times
 @param tokens The addresses of the ERC20 tokens
 @param amounts The amounts of tokens to deposit
 @param signatures The signatures of the permits
 @param deadlines The deadlines of the permits
 @dev This function should be call by owner but opens for donation
		and reverts if the length of the three arrays are not equal
		or if any of the depositTokenSig() calls reverts

@notice Withdraws ERC20 tokens from the contract
 @param token The address of the ERC20 token
 @param amount The amount of tokens to withdraw
 @param all If true, withdraws all amount of the given type
 @dev This function is only callable by the owner

@notice Returns the balance of the given token
 @param token The address of the ERC20 token
 @return The balance of the given token

@notice Returns the domain separator
 @return The domain separator
 @dev This value is used for signature validation
		by the EIP-712 standard
		(https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-712)
